# Naming Conventions

Follow these conventions for all new and renamed files and constants.

**Placeholder names** (`items`, `orders`, `<domain>`) illustrate patterns — use your product’s module names.

## Pages, Layouts & Components (`.tsx`)

- **Convention:** PascalCase
- **Examples:** `LoginPage.tsx`, `DashboardLayout.tsx`, `AppSidebar.tsx`, `RootLayout.tsx`
- **Exception:** Do not rename files under `src/components/ui/` — they follow shadcn’s default (e.g. `button.tsx`, `dropdown-menu.tsx`). New components outside `components/ui` use PascalCase.
- **Imports (bundle size)** — Prefer **direct imports** from the implementing module over heavy **barrel** entry points (`export *` / large `index` re-exports) when a package pulls in a huge dependency graph (common with icon packs, some UI kits, `lodash`, `date-fns` barrel entries). Keeps dev cold start and production chunks leaner; use your bundler’s import optimization if it offers one.
- **No nested component definitions** — Do not declare React components inside another component’s function body. That creates a new component type every render, so React **remounts** children (lost input focus, repeated effects, broken animations). Hoist child components to module scope and pass data via props (or `useCallback` + stable children only when appropriate).

## Hooks (custom hooks & TanStack Query hooks)

### Domain modules (`src/lib/<domain>/`)

- **File name:** camelCase — `mapItem.ts`, `validateItemWizard.ts`, `useItemWizard.ts`, `itemWizardCtx.types.ts`
- **Purpose:** Mappers, pure validation, multi-step orchestration hooks, and domain-specific wiring types shared across pages.
- **Exported hooks:** camelCase with `use` prefix — `useItemWizard`, `useItemWizardState`
- **Do not** use kebab-case `use-*.ts` here — that pattern is for **`src/api/features/`** and **`src/lib/hooks/`** only.

### Page-local hooks (`src/pages/**`)

- **Avoid** — prefer `src/lib/<domain>/` for orchestration hooks. Pages keep **components** and thin **React context providers** only.

### App / shared UI hooks (`src/lib/hooks/`)

- **File name:** kebab-case after the `use-` prefix: `use-<name>.ts`
- **Examples:** `use-debounce.ts`, `use-mobile.tsx`
- **Location:** `src/lib/hooks/`

### API feature modules (`src/api/features/<domain>/`)

Each backend domain gets one folder with **prefixed filenames**:

| File | Purpose | Example |
| ---- | ------- | ------- |
| `<domain>.service.ts` | HTTP functions (no React) | `items.service.ts` → `getItems` |
| `<domain>.schema.ts` | Zod + `z.infer` types | `items.schema.ts` |
| `<domain>.types.ts` | Optional DTO re-exports | `items.types.ts` |
| `use-<domain>.ts` | TanStack Query hooks | `use-items.ts` → `useItems` |

| Scope | Folder | Example |
| ----- | ------ | ------- |
| **Domain module** | `features/<domain>/` | `features/items/` |
| **Surface + domain** | `features/<segment>/<domain>/` | `features/admin/reports/` |
| **Cross-cutting** | `features/auth/` (same file set) | `auth.service.ts`, `use-auth.ts` |

Rules:

- **Folder name:** lowercase / kebab-case — `items`, `payment-methods`.
- **Query hook file:** `use-<kebab-domain>.ts`; **exported hook:** camelCase with `use` prefix (`useItems`, `useAuthMe`).
- Include **surface or domain** in the exported hook name when ambiguity would hurt (`useAdminOrders` vs `useStorefrontOrders`).
- Do **not** suffix with `Mutation` or `Query` — name by intent.
- **Do not** repeat the segment in the filename when the file already lives under `features/<segment>/` (same rule as before for nested segments).

Shared-only paths (not feature-owned):

- `src/api/schema/primitives.schema.ts` — shared Zod primitives
- `src/api/types/global.types.ts` — `ApiSuccess`, pagination, cross-feature wrappers
- `src/api/lib/` — optional `use-authenticated-query.ts` and similar helpers

## API services / schemas / types (legacy layout)

**Do not** add new domain files under flat `src/api/services/`, `src/api/queries/`, or `src/api/schema/<domain>.schema.ts`. Use **`src/api/features/<domain>/`** instead.

## Type-only modules (non-API)

- **File name:** `<name>.types.ts`
- **Location:** colocated types elsewhere — follow the same `*.types.ts` pattern.

## Utility & Logic Files (`.ts`)

- **Convention:** camelCase
- **Examples:** `mockData.ts`, `authStore.ts`, `formatCurrency.ts`
- **Applies to:** utils (`src/lib/utils/`: e.g. `cn.ts`, `date.ts`), stores, validations (`src/lib/validations/`), constants (`src/lib/constants/`), **domain helper folders** (`src/lib/<domain>/` — camelCase filenames like `buildCheckoutPayload.ts`), and other non-component modules (excluding hooks and `*.types.ts` files above)

## Providers (React context / app wrappers)

- **Location:** `src/providers/` (e.g. TanStack Query, auth, theme)
- **Convention:** PascalCase for component files (e.g. `AuthProvider.tsx`, `QueryProvider.tsx`)

## Constants

- **In code:** UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (e.g. `MAX_RETRIES`, `DEFAULT_PAGE_SIZE`)
- **Location:** `src/lib/constants/`; file names stay camelCase

## Route guards / layout-level components

- **Location:** `src/components/guards/` (e.g. `ProtectedRoute.tsx` — props like `guestOnly` or `requiredRole` as your app needs)

## Page structure (colocate page-specific components)

See **`page-composition.mdc`** for size limits, folder layout, and split triggers when pages grow past ~750 lines.

- **Folders under `src/pages/` are lowercase** (or kebab-case for multi-word routes) — e.g. `pages/creator/account/`, `pages/home/`, `pages/public/`. **Do not** use PascalCase folders like `pages/HomePage/`.
- **Page component files** are PascalCase and live in the route folder — e.g. `pages/home/HomePage.tsx`, `pages/creator/account/AccountPage.tsx`.
- **`index.tsx`** is optional when a page has many colocated children — e.g. `pages/shared/referral/ReferralPage/index.tsx` (folder name may match the page for that pattern only).
- **One folder per URL area** when routes share a base path — colocate list, detail, and modals (e.g. `pages/app/orders/OrdersPage.tsx`, `OrderDetailPage.tsx`).
- **Orchestration hooks** — live in `src/lib/<domain>/` (see **Hooks** above); pages keep components and thin React context providers.
- **Page-only helpers** — Pure functions unlikely to be reused may stay in the page file **below** the default export, using `function helperName() { ... }`. **Reusable** logic belongs under **`src/lib/<domain>/`**; domain types belong in **`src/api/features/<domain>/`** (not `src/pages/`).

## Folders

- Use **lowercase** for single words: `admin`, `app`, `utils`, `hooks`
- Use **kebab-case** for multi-word folders when helpful (`payment-methods`, `mock-data`)
- Under `src/api/`, **feature folder names** match backend modules (`features/items/`, `features/billing/`). Optional surface segments: `features/admin/…`.
- **Static asset file names** under `src/assets/` — kebab-case (e.g. `logo-dark.svg`). Icon and SVG *usage* — see `icons-and-assets.mdc`.

## Quick Reference

| Type                                                       | Convention                                        | Example                    |
| ---------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------- |
| Page folders (`src/pages/`)                                | lowercase / kebab-case                            | `home`, `creator/account`  |
| Page component files                                       | PascalCase                                        | `HomePage.tsx`             |
| Domain orchestration hook (`src/lib/<domain>/`)              | camelCase `use*.ts`                               | `useItemWizard.ts`         |
| Layout / component (`.tsx`, except `components/ui`)        | PascalCase                                        | `AppSidebar.tsx`           |
| API feature folder                                         | `features/<domain>/`                              | `features/items/`          |
| API service / schema / types (in feature)                  | `<domain>.service.ts`, `.schema.ts`, `.types.ts`  | `items.service.ts`         |
| API query hook (in feature)                                | `use-<domain>.ts` under `features/<domain>/`      | `use-items.ts`             |
| Shared API schema / types                                  | `api/schema/`, `api/types/` at root               | `primitives.schema.ts`     |
| Hook files (`src/lib/hooks`)                               | `use-<kebab>.ts`                                  | `use-debounce.ts`          |
| Type modules                                               | `<name>.types.ts`                                 | `auth.types.ts`            |
| Utility / logic (`.ts`)                                    | camelCase                                         | `mockData.ts`              |
| Domain helpers (`lib/<domain>/`)                           | camelCase                                         | `buildCheckoutPayload.ts`  |
| Constants                                                  | UPPER_SNAKE_CASE                                  | `MAX_RETRIES`              |
| Folders                                                    | lowercase / kebab-case                            | `admin`, `payment-methods` |
| Static assets (`src/assets/`)                              | kebab-case filenames                              | `logo-dark.svg`            |
